00:02:55.610 --> 00:02:58.760
So why is the case of mercury
interesting in the context

00:02:58.760 --> 00:03:01.820
of sort of international
business supply

00:03:01.820 --> 00:03:03.930
chain regulation?

00:03:03.930 --> 00:03:06.640
Well, mercury is the
latest, the most recent

00:03:06.640 --> 00:03:08.596
global environmental treaty.

00:03:08.596 --> 00:03:09.970
So the Minamata
Convention, which

00:03:09.970 --> 00:03:13.280
is an international
convention on Mercury,

00:03:13.280 --> 00:03:17.240
was signed just this
past October, 2013.

00:03:17.240 --> 00:03:20.840
And it is widely
thought of as it's

00:03:20.840 --> 00:03:23.900
the first real new global
environmental treaty

00:03:23.900 --> 00:03:25.150
in over a decade.

00:03:25.150 --> 00:03:27.860
The previous one was also on
a chemicals related topic,

00:03:27.860 --> 00:03:29.990
the Stockholm Convention.

00:03:29.990 --> 00:03:32.580
So it's an example of
international environmental

00:03:32.580 --> 00:03:34.330
cooperation of which
we don't have a lot.

00:03:34.330 --> 00:03:36.954
We don't have a lot of concrete
stuff coming out of the climate

00:03:36.954 --> 00:03:38.370
negotiations right now.

00:03:38.370 --> 00:03:41.790
But this is a brand new
agreed global treaty.

00:03:41.790 --> 00:03:45.520
And it's widely thought of
as the first entire life

00:03:45.520 --> 00:03:48.440
cycle international convention.

00:03:48.440 --> 00:03:50.970
So I'm going to talk
about that in that context

00:03:50.970 --> 00:03:54.860
and how it emerged, what some
of the science behind it is,

00:03:54.860 --> 00:04:00.070
and how it might influence
thinking about chemicals

00:04:00.070 --> 00:04:03.800
regulation in a product
context, because products

00:04:03.800 --> 00:04:06.990
are a core area--
mercury in products

00:04:06.990 --> 00:04:09.480
are a core area of
mercury regulation

00:04:09.480 --> 00:04:10.927
under the convention.

00:04:10.927 --> 00:04:13.010
I'm going to talk a little
bit about the interface

00:04:13.010 --> 00:04:15.110
as well between
domestic regulation

00:04:15.110 --> 00:04:17.720
in the US,
international regulation

00:04:17.720 --> 00:04:19.480
in the European
Union context, which

00:04:19.480 --> 00:04:23.030
sort of is a
sub-global regulation,

00:04:23.030 --> 00:04:25.420
and how that interfaces
with the global context.

00:04:25.420 --> 00:04:27.290
So that's sort of where
I'm planning to go.

00:04:27.290 --> 00:04:29.540
Please feel free to interrupt
me if you have questions

00:04:29.540 --> 00:04:32.115
or want to go in
